  "text": "The constructed systems of linear equations are solved by the quasi-minimal residual (QMR) method [CITATION_1] , which is another Krylov subspace method. GMRES that was used in Sec. 3 to solve a 2D problem is not suitable for 3D problems here because it requires too much memory [CITATION_2] .",
